Detailed Description

Compute the kinematic jacobian.

Implementation of an algorithm that checks whether a node is an ancestor of another one or not.

Implementation of two algorithms that check whether a node is NP (no parent) or not and if it has a parent or not.

Implementation of an algorithm that computes the deepest common ancestor of two nodes.

Implementation of articular jacobian of point given an influencing chain of joints.

i.e. the matrix J such that J*dq is the vertical concatenation of each body spatial motion vector (in the moving body frame)
